HEADWORD: Pattee
<hw>Pat*tee"</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>patt⟦eacute⟧</ets>,
fem. <ets>patt⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, fr. <ets>patte</ets> paw, foot. Cf.
<er>Patten</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Narrow at the inner, and
very broad at the other, end, or having its arms of that shape; -- said
of a cross. See <xex>Illust.</xex> (8) of <er>Cross</er>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>pat⟦eacute⟧</asp>,
<asp>patee</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

